page.title: 01Area Description
page.content:
The area of this Domesday square can be divided into three broad types of environment, namely; a) the coastal zone comprising of approximately 3.4km of the south eastern coastline of the Kingdom of Fife; b) the rural zone inland, which makes up the majority of this area, consisting primarily of high quality agricultural land with a few areas of mixed woodland; c) the coastal settlements of East Wemyss and Buckhaven.
There is one street of Coaltown of Wemyss in the south east corner of this Domesday square, however, the majority of Coaltown is within the Domesday square 03320693 therefore it will only be dealt with briefley here.
